paragraph.subSubSection:
Descriptive notes. Head-body 74-146 mm, tail 62-120 mm, ear 14-20 mm, hindfoot 20-25 mm; weight 10-91 g. Fur of Hubert’s Multimammate Mouse is dark gray (young) to rusty brown (old) or blackish (
Senegal
) above, dark below. Tail is long (c.84% of head-body length) and scaly, dark above and sometimes paler below. Forefeet and hindfeet are whitish. Females have twelve pairs of nipples. Chromosomal complement is 2n = 32 and FN = 44-46.
